description: Award winning novelist. He debuted in America with the 2006 English-translated release of his story, The Crimson Labyrinth (1999). His works include more than ten books and five films. His novel Shin Sekai Yori (From the New World) published in 2008, earned the Japan SF award for that year. The story was subsequently adapted into a twenty-five episode anime by A-1 Pictures, airing from September 2012 to March 2013. It is now being adapted into a manga illustrated by Tōru Oikawa and is ongoing as of May '14.
name: Yusuke Kishi
